<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Emami-Kashani Notes Muslim `Indifference' in Sermon </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502143294 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1204 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2502143294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Second Friday prayers sermon by Ayatollah Mohammad </F>
Emami-Kashani, interim Friday prayers leader, in Tehran on 25 
February -- recorded] 
  [Excerpts] [passage omitted] The people have become 
indifferent toward their own destiny, and the destiny of the 
world of Islam; for example, the government of the Islamic 
Republic of Iran has once again declared its readiness to send 
troops to Bosnia- Herzegovina to act as peacekeeping forces. If 
the world Muslims gave only one-tenth of the importance that the 
Islamic Republic gives to the Bosnian Muslims, and if the 
governments of other Islamic countries possessed only 
one-hundredth of the resolute will that our Islamic system has 
in its attitude toward the conditions of Muslims in that country 
-- as well as Muslims in Palestine and other parts of the world 
-- then the situation in Bosnia, or for that matter Palestine 
and other parts of the Islamic world would have been totally 
different today. 
  It is because of indifference that we have this situation 
today. In particular, during this auspicious month of Ramadan, 
the great number of preachers who deliver so many Friday prayer 
sermons in so many great and splendid mosques throughout the 
vast land of Islam must undertake efforts to make the people 
aware of their issues and inform them about what the world is 
doing to them: that is that world arrogance is taking control of 
some Muslim countries while at the same time attempting to bring 
the rest of them under its control too. It is one of our duties 
to make people fully aware of such matters. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

