<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Authorities Report on Recent Security Incidents </TI></H3>
<H4>   5 Deaths, 12 Arrests Reported </H4>
<F P=102> LD0203181294 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 1700 
GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0203181294 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The security services today announced that five 
people were killed in the past 72 hours in a number of 
provinces. Among the victims was a 17-year-old secondary school 
student who was assassinated outside her home in the new council 
estate in the municipality of Meftah in Blida Province. Four 
gunmen forced their way into the home of a 62-year-old woman 
named Derradj Adjouba and killed her with a knife. A teacher of 
the Koran was shot dead in the municipality of Meddah in Chlef. 
In Algiers, the bodies of a customs officer and his wife were 
discovered in a council estate consisting of 310 apartments 
situated at the Gue de Constantine. 
  In addition, the security services also announced the arrest 
of 12 members of armed groups in the provinces of Mila, Algiers, 
Djelfa, and Boumerdes. In western Algeria, three municipal 
buildings, one farmer's market, and two parking lots were set on 
fire in Relizane and Sidi Bel Abbes. 

</TEXT>

