<H3> <TI>   Parties Condemn Hebron Incident, Issue Statements </TI></H3>
<H4>   Opposition Parties `Strongly' Condemn </H4>
<F P=102> NC0303220994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1710 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0303220994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 3 Mar (MENA)--The opposition parties have 
strongly condemned the ugly crime the Israelis committed in the 
al-Ibrahimi Mosque on Friday last week in which scores of 
innocent Palestinians were martyred. 
  The statement, which was issued by the parties today during 
a 
news conference held at the headquarters of the Liberal Party, 
asked that the world conscience be addressed by sending cables 
of protest to the member countries of the Security Council to 
impose economic sanctions on Israel and force it to respect the 
Palestinians. 
  The statement asked the Islamic Conference Organization to 
convene an urgent conference in holy Mecca to discuss what the 
Muslims are being subjected to in Palestine and all other 
places, especially Bosnia-Herzegovina, and make practical 
decisions to protect the holy Muslim shrines, especially inside 
the al-Aqsa Mosque. 

</TEXT>

