<H3> <TI>   Groups Demonstrate To Protest Hebron Incident </TI></H3>
<H4>   Tear Gas Used to Disperse Students </H4>
<F P=102> NC0303150194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1443 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0303150194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 3 Mar (MENA)--Hundreds of university students 
assembled in al-Tahrir Square this afternoon carrying placards 
condemning the ugly massacre inside the al-Ibrahimi Mosque in 
Hebron last Friday [25 February]. 
  The students denounced this painful incident and demanded a 
halt to the peace negotiations with Israel. 
  After one hour of slogan shouting, when the square became 
overcrowded with other citizens, the police dispersed the 
demonstrators in order to prevent other elements infiltrating 
them and to keep traffic moving as it had begun to be disrupted. 
The police used tear gas and some warning shots to disperse the 
demonstrators. 

</TEXT>

