<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bomb Explodes Outside Egyptian-American Bank </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0303182394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1730 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0303182394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 3 Mar (MENA)--A small explosive device went 
off at around 1820 [1620 GMT] this evening at the bottom of the 
stairs leading to the Egyptian-American Bank on al-Batal Ahmad 
'Abd-al-'Aziz Street in al-Muhandisin district [of Cairo]. 
  The explosion caused minor damage to some windows and the 
entrance stairs. No one was injured. 
  Security men from the al-Jizah Security Department and 
forensic experts went to the scene of the crime to collect 
evidence at the site and the prosecution office has started 
investigations. 

</TEXT>

