<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Organizations Accused of Forming Antiregime Plots </TI></H3>
<H4>   Damietta Mayor Charged </H4>
<F P=102> NC0203200694 Cairo AL-AHRAM in Arabic 25 Feb 94 p 14 </F>
<F P=103> NC0203200694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-AHRAM </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by 'Ali Dawud from Damietta] </F>
  [Excerpt] Mustafah al-Badawayhi, head of the Damietta 
prosecution office, has ordered that the mayor of Damietta, a 
member of the city council, and 15 other extremists be put in 
prison for 15 days pending investigations. They were charged 
with forming a secret organization with the objective of 
toppling the government by using the position of the mayor 
supported by a number of other members of the council who belong 
to the Labor Party to conduct secret activities and to use the 
summer resort of Ra's al-Barr, which is now empty, for their 
organization's training, lectures, and other instruction. 
  The security men noticed some suspect activities by some 
youths known for their extremist tendencies. By observing them, 
it became evident that they were forming a secret organization 
and that the mayor was abusing his office to support the 
organization. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

