<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Court Continues To Hear Defense in Sidqi Case </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2702174894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1702 GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2702174894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Cairo, 27 Feb (MENA)--The Supreme Military Court 
today continued to hear the defense plea in the case of the 
attempt to assassinate Prime Minister Dr. 'Atif Sidqi, which 
involves 15 defendants, including six being tried in absentia. 
  The lawyer for the sixth defendant, 'Isam Muhammad 
'Abd-al-Rahman, called for the examination of all the defendants 
to verify the claim that they were assaulted. He said that he 
joins the other lawyers in demanding that the court disqualify 
all the testimonies attributed to the defendants. 
  Husayn Jabir Muhammad, the defense lawyer for the 11th 
defendant, Tuhami Ahmad 'Abdallah, called on the court to find 
his client not guilty for various reasons, including the 
invalidity of the arrest and search warrant because it was 
issued two hours after the accused were arrested and the 
invalidity of the testimonies and admissions attributed to him 
because they were taken under coercion. [passage omitted] 
  The court adjourned until tomorrow, when it will continue to 
hear the defense case. 

</TEXT>

