<F P=100> Morocco </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Condemns Hebron Mosque Massacre </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602013894 Rabat Moroccan Kingdom Radio Network in Arabic 
2300 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2602013894 </F>
<F P=104>  Rabat Moroccan Kingdom Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An official spokesman for the Ministry of Foreign 
Affairs and Cooperation said that the Kingdom of Morocco learned 
with deep sorrow and grief of the massacre in Hebron of dozens 
of innocent Palestinians who were performing their religious 
rites in the venerated month of Ramadan and in a place sacred to 
the revealed religions. 
  The official spokesman added that Morocco, as it pays homage 
to the souls of the martyrs, who were martyrs of blind 
extremism, strongly condemns this hideous crime which was 
perpetrated at a time when the international organizations were 
expecting that peace would soon prevail in the region and were 
according particular importance to the recent 
Palestinian-Israeli agreement. 
  The spokesman concluded by saying that Morocco, while 
calling 
for the perpetrators of this hideous crime to be severely and 
decisively punished and for the escalation of violence to be 
halted, considers that such acts must be an incentive to 
international organizations to make preparations for 
guaranteeing peace, security, and the legitimate rights of the 
Palestinian people. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

