<H3> <TI>   Al-Bid Holds Phone Conversation With King Husayn </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA0203165294 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1400 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0203165294 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid, the deputy chairman of 
the Presidential Council, last night had a telephone 
conversation with his brother, King al-Husayn Bin-Talal, king of 
the Hashemite Kingdom of Jordan, on the intimate fraternal 
relations between the two fraternal countries and the latest 
developments in the national arena since the signing of the 
document of pledge and accord in addition to developments 
affecting Arab affairs. The brother deputy chairman of the 
Presidential Council reaffirmed the importance of adhering to 
the document of pledge and accord and accelerating its 
implementation. He expressed thanks and appreciation to His 
Majesty King al-Husayn and to all the brothers in Jordan for 
their commendable efforts to help our country emerge from its 
current predicament. He also expressed thanks for efforts made 
to create conditions conducive to ending the military and 
security deterioration and for starting to (?implement) the 
document of pledge and accord. 

</TEXT>

