<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Bid Meets With Military, Security Commanders </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0303202994 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
2000 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0303202994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid, vice chairman of the 
Presidential Council and secretary general of the Yemeni 
Socialist Party, met this afternoon with the brother commanders 
of the military units and security agencies and the commanders 
of military police in the commercial and economic capital, Aden. 
  He made a speech in which he expressed eagerness to meet 
with 
them 11 days after the accord document was finally signed. He 
expressed thanks and appreciation for the efforts made by the 
Jordanian and Omani brothers, the Arab League secretary general, 
and all the friends in the European Community and the United 
States for helping our country to overcome the challenges that 
faced the march of unity and democracy and the building of a 
modern Yemeni state. 
  The vice chairman of the Presidential Council asserted that 
by signing the document, the Yemeni people have proven they can 
rely on dialogue and reason. He urged all sincere members of 
the dialogue committee, as well as those not on the committee, 
to adhere to the accord document and work toward implementing it. 

</TEXT>

