<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Committee: Units' Return to Camps `Proceeding Well' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0303175594 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0303175594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The higher joint military committee, which is made 
up of the deputy chiefs of staff for operations and logistics, 
the heads of the Jordanian and the Omani military committees, 
and the U.S. and French military attaches, has held a meeting. 
It reviewed the military situation and the extent of the 
commitment to the implementation of the military document issued 
by the brother chairman and vice chairman of the Presidential 
Council on the need for the return of all military units to 
their positions before the crisis. 
  The committee discussed the results of the field action and 
the extent of the military units' commitment to implementation 
through the reports submitted by the subcommittees supervising 
field activity. 
  The higher joint military committee asserts that the return 
to previous positions is proceeding well in Ta'izz, Lahd, Abyan, 
and Ibb. The committee has great confidence that the leaders of 
the groups and units in the rest of the regions have started to 
return to the agreed-upon locations. 
  The committee has decided to form a third subcommittee to 
supervise and monitor the return of units to their previous 
positions in Ma'rib and Shabwah. This subcommittee will start 
work tomorrow morning. 
  The higher military committee urges the brother [words 
indistinct] maximum degree of cooperation to facilitate the work 
of the subcommittees by carrying out the decisions issued to 
them in executive orders from the defense minister and the chief 
of the General Staff. 
  The higher military committee is working around the clock. 
It reassures the Yemeni people that there is a spirit of 
cooperation and accord between its sons and that everyone is 
concerned about the unity and cohesion of the Armed Forces to 
preserve Yemeni national unity. 

</TEXT>

