<F P=102>  NC0303172894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1615 GMT 3 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0303172894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Evening Newsreel" program] </F>
  [Text] Referring to the agreement with the PLO, Prime 
Minister Yitzhaq Rabin said today that if the negotiations are 
resumed, we can reach an agreement within one month. 
  [Begin Rabin recording] I was aware that Hamas and the 
Islamic Jihad on the Palestinian side will do everything to 
intensify terrorism and kill Israelis--and I stress Israelis, 
and my intention is Israeli Jews and non-Jews. Furthermore, I 
was aware that there is friction, and there was friction, with 
settlers, particularly with the most radical--the members of the 
Kakh and Kahane Hay groups and their supporters. But I admit it 
was difficult to imagine that such a hideous murder would be 
perpetrated by an Israeli--and what is more, one who wears a 
cap. I did not imagine that there would also be an Israeli 
Hamas or Jewish Hamas. I appeal to the Palestinians and their 
leadership in Tunis: I understand the pain and the anger. 
Don't allow a lone Jewish murderer who killed Palestinian 
Muslims just for being who they were, during prayers, to destroy 
the prospect for peace. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

