<H3> <TI>   Peres on Talks With Tarnoff </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0403112794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1000 GMT 4 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0403112794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres said following his 
talks with U.S. Undersecretary of State Peter Tarnoff that 
Israel is ready to come to terms with the Palestinians and 
supports the establishment of a strong Palestinian police. Our 
political correspondent Shlomo Raz says Peres' statement 
apparently means that Israel is prepared to restrict the number 
of Palestinian policemen to more than 8,000. The prime minister 
has recently said that this is the figure that Israel has agrees 
to. 
  Regarding foreign presence in the territories, the foreign 
minister said Israel agrees to this according to the Declaration 
of Principles. In the foreign minister's opinion, it is 
possible to successfully conclude the negotiations with the 
Palestinians within one month. 
  Our correspondent adds that the situation in Russia was also 
discussed in the meeting. 

</TEXT>

