<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   `More Than 30' Palestinians Shot, Wounded by IDF </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0303215794 Paris AFP in English 2057 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0303215794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Jerusalem, March 3 (AFP) -- Israeli troops shot 
and wounded more than 30 Palestinians in the West Bank and Gaza 
Strip on Thursday [3 March], but the level of violence was down 
from the previous days after the Hebron massacre. 
  Palestinian sources said 27 people were shot in the West 
Bank, including 10 in a clash between troops and demonstrators 
in the village of Nahalian near Bethlehem. 
  Seven Arabs were hit by army bullets in Gaza, they said. 
Also on the strip, an alleged collaborator with the Israelis 
was killed. PLO chief Yasir 'Arafat's mainstream Fatah group 
claimed responsibility for the killing of Salim Alibani, who was 
40. [passage omitted] 
  The army also sealed off the territories on Sunday 
preventing 
70,000 Palestinians from reaching their jobs in Israel. The 
closure is to be enforced for another week, according to Israeli 
television. 
  Troops were on alert for Friday, the day of Moslem prayers 
and a week after the Hebron killings. 

</TEXT>

