<F P=102>  JN0303191294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Arabic 1530 GMT 3 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0303191294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The official committee formed to investigate the 
Hebron massacre held its first meeting this evening at the 
Higher Court building in the capital. 
  The purpose of the meeting was to make technical 
arrangements 
for the committee's work prior to its first public meetings next 
week. 
  Attorney Shomo'el Kassar has made an appeal to the Higher 
Court of Justice asking it to issue an order to prevent the 
official committee from beginning investigations into the 
criminal incident that took place at the holy Ibrahimi Mosque in 
Hebron. 
  The appeal said investigating this case is wholly rejected, 
since, to date, no committee of inquiry has been formed to 
investigate several bloody incidents against Jewish citizens. 
  Our legal affairs correspondent Moshe Matlih said Attorney 
Kassar attributes the formation of the committee to political 
reasons. 

