<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Telecommunications Disruptions Continue in Areas </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0403085594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0800 GMT 4 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0403085594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] There are serious disruptions in telephone service 
in the country. Many of the telephone lines have been 
disconnected by the striking Bezeq Company employees. Many of 
the problems and disconnections have been deliberately made by 
the company employees, the company's director general said this 
morning. The company will establish an inspection committee, 
and if employees are found to be guilty of malicious action 
against the telephone network, disciplinary and even judicial 
measures will be taken against them. 
  Meanwhile, our correspondent Meron Tzur reports that there 
are difficulties in dialing from inside and outside the country. 
This includes, among others, facsimile and some computer 
communications. Employees have returned to normal work only in 
the Haifa District and the north. The company is considering 
distributing back-to-work orders to the employees to ensure 
vital services. It is also awaiting an answer from the 
employees committee on a compromise proposal made last night. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

