<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peace Negotiators Return From Washington </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0303171394 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1610 GMT 3 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0303171394 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Members of the Jordanian delegation to the 
Jordanian-Israeli peace talks have returned to Amman from 
Washington. Delegation member Marwan Dudin said the delegation's 
return came in the wake of a Jordanian decision, in coordination 
with the other Arab parties, on suspending the current round of 
negotiations as part of the manifestations of protest and anger 
that prevailed among the official and popular circles in Jordan 
following the savage massacre against the worshipers at the holy 
Ibrahimi Mosque last Friday. 
  The decision to suspend the negotiations was made at the 
government's instructions after holding intensive Arab contacts. 

</TEXT>

