<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Greek Foreign Minister Papoulias on Official Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Arrives, Makes Statement </H4>
<F P=102> JN0203205894 Amman Jordan Television Network in English 2000 
GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0203205894 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Jordan Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "News at Ten" program] </F>
  [Text] Greek Foreign Minister Karolos Papoulias arrived in 
Jordan on a visit, which will include talks on bilateral 
relations and the Middle East peace process. The Greek minister 
is the current chairman of the European Union Council of 
Ministers. He arrived in Amman after visits to Israel and the 
PLO headquarters in Tunis. 
  He told Jordan Television that he will discuss with 
Jordanian 
officials current conditions in the Middle East in the wake of 
the Hebron massacre. He said the most pressing issue now is to 
maintain the momentum of the peace process. 
  The Greek foreign minister added that the European Union 
believes that a demand by the Palestinians in the occupied lands 
for international protection is just one. 

</TEXT>

