<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Greek Foreign Minister Papoulias on Official Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Received by Prime Minister </H4>
<F P=102> JN0303151994 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1200 GMT 3 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0303151994 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali received 
at the Prime Ministry this morning Karolos Papoulias, Greek 
foreign minister and chairman of the European Community [EC] 
Council of Ministers, and the delegation accompanying him. 
  Their discussion dealt with bilateral relations and the 
existing cooperation between Jordan and the EC countries, ways 
of enhancing them, as well as the most important issues in the 
international arena. 
  In a press statement on the most important ideas he 
communicated to the Israeli leaders on behalf of the Palestinian 
president, Papoulias said: These ideas revolve around calming 
the atmosphere and creating a new atmosphere that would 
facilitate things, provide security for the Palestinians, and 
lead to disarming the settlers and resuming the dialogue between 
the two sides. He said that the Israeli side has promised to 
take these ideas into consideration and will reply to them 
later. He said: Efforts will be exerted in the future and the 
EC hopes that the peace efforts will produce good results and 
will not reach a dead end. 
  The meeting was attended by Talal Sat'an al-Hasan, minister 
of state for foreign affairs; Dr. Fawwaz Abu-al-Ghanam, minister 
of state; the Jordanian ambassador to Greece; the Greek 
ambassador to Jordan; and the EC representative in Amman. 

</TEXT>

