<H3> <TI>   Greek Foreign Minister Papoulias on Official Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Confers With Planning Minister </H4>
<F P=102> JN0303194594 Amman PETRA-JNA in Arabic 1600 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0303194594 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman PETRA-JNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Amman, 3 Mar (PETRA)--Planning Minister Dr. 
Ziyad Fariz today received Karolos Papoulias, Greek foreign 
minister and chairman of the EC Council of Ministers, and his 
delegation. 
  Dr. Fariz reviewed the challenges Jordan is facing in the 
current phase, the circumstances prevailing in the region, the 
economic measures Jordan has adopted, and the achievements it 
has realized. He also reviewed the repercussions of the Gulf 
crisis, including the decline in Jordanian exports to the Gulf 
states and the reduced demand for Jordanian workers in these 
states. [passage omitted] 
  Dr. Fariz noted his appreciation for the EC aid to Jordan, 
and urged the EC to further support Jordan in the economic field 
in order to fill the 1994 financial gap and alleviate the burden 
of the general indebtedness. [passage omitted] 
  Dr. Fariz also reviewed Jordanian-Greek relations in the 
economic, trade, technical, and cultural fields based on the 
bilateral cooperation agreement signed in 1976. He discussed 
with the guest minister ways to activate bilateral cooperation 
by establishing joint food and agricultural industries, and 
holding meetings between businessmen from both countries to 
explore new ideas and promote cooperation in various fields. 
  The guest minister noted the extent of identity between the 
objectives of the Jordanian development plans and those which 
the EC is seeking to achieve in order to encourage 
competitiveness and fight both unemployment and poverty. He 
said he highly appreciated the great efficiency Jordan is 
enjoying in the field of economic and other policies. He noted 
that Jordan will be supported by the EC in various fields. 

</TEXT>

