<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Greek Foreign Minister Papoulias on Official Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Delivers Letters to King Husayn </H4>
<F P=102> JN0303172994 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1600 GMT 3 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0303172994 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In the presence of His Highness Crown Prince Hasan, 
His Majesty King Husayn received Karolos Papoulias, Greek 
foreign minister and the current chairman of the EC Council of 
Ministers at the Royal Hashemite Court today. 
  Papoulias conveyed to his majesty an oral message from Greek 
President Konstandinos Karamanlis, a letter from the EC, and a 
letter from Greek Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou. The guest 
minister also conveyed to His Majesty King Husayn the Greek 
president's greetings and appreciation for his majesty's great 
role in maintaining security and stability in this region that 
has suffered from tension and conflict for decades. 
  The EC's letter contained the EC's great appreciation for 
the 
continued sincere efforts that his majesty made to achieve 
Yemeni reconciliation and support the unanimous signing of the 
document of accord by key Yemeni figures, bodies, and parties. 
  The letter emphasized that the EC looks forward to continued 
efforts by his majesty to implement and turn into tangible 
reality the articles of the Yemeni accord document in order to 
safeguard Yemen's unity and consolidate its democratic march in 
an atmosphere of security and stability. 
  The Greek foreign minister also handed his majesty a letter 
from the Greek prime minister. The letter contained 
Papandreou's admiration of the distinguished and responsible 
role that His Majesty King Husayn has played for many years in 
terms of maintaining security and stability in the Middle East. 
The letter also contained the appreciation by Papandreou and 
his government for his majesty's continued efforts to achieve a 
comprehensive, just, and lasting peace in the region based on 
international legitimacy and the Security Council resolutions. 
  In his letter to King Husayn, Papandreou stressed his 
appreciation and admiration for the great success that his 
majesty achieved by reconciling the disputing Yemeni parties, 
holding the signing the document of accord, and beginning the 
implementation of its articles out of his care for Yemen's unity 
and achievements and in order to protect its security and 
stability. 
  The letter also stressed the deep Jordanian-Greek relations 
and the need to consolidate and promote them to serve the 
interests of both friendly peoples. 
  Papandreou's letter also pointed to the distinguished 
efforts 
his majesty is making to achieve a comprehensive and just peace 
in the region. The letter emphasized that these efforts are 
appreciated by the Greek Government. 
  The meeting was attended by His Excellency al-Sharif Zayd 
Bin-Shakir, chief of the Royal Hashemite Court; Marwan al-Qasim, 
his majesty the king's political adviser; Talal Sat'an al-Hasan, 
minister of state for foreign affairs; and Amjad al-Majali, the 
Jordanian ambassador to Greece. It was also attended by the 
Greek Foreign Ministry secretary general, the Greek ambassador 
in Amman, and the EC ambassador in Amman. 

</TEXT>

