<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Labor Minister Urges ILO To Implement Decisions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0303200594 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1600 GMT 3 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0303200594 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Labor Minister Khalid al-Ghizawi has chaired a 
meeting comprising an International Labor Organization [ILO] 
fact-finding team and representatives of the Royal Committee for 
Jerusalem Affairs, the Palestinian Affairs Department, the Amman 
Chamber of Industry, the Trade Union Federation, and the Union 
of the Chambers of Commerce at the meetings hall in the Ministry 
of Labor. 
  During the meeting, the labor minister delivered a statement 
urging the ILO to implement the decisions made by the 
international labor conferences in 1974 and 1980. These 
decisions call for extending all forms of aid to the Palestinian 
people and their labor forces in order to support their 
steadfastness on their land. [passage omitted] 
  Minister al-Ghizawi noted the inhumane policy that Israel is 
pursuing in the occupied Arab territories. He said: We in 
Jordan only recognize the sovereignty of God Almighty over the 
Islamic holy places. He also pointed to Israel's policy, which 
aims to Judaize Jerusalem, and, consequently, complete the 
greater Jerusalem project. The minister added that Jordan 
condemns and vehemently denounces all forms of Judaization, and 
urges the international bodies to intervene in order to protect 
the mosques and churches, so that they will be outside the 
framework of the bloody conflict. 
  He said that Jordan also demands a halt to the building of 
Israeli settlements, the disarming of the settlers, and a total 
transfer of the settlers from the West Bank and Gaza Strip. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

