<DOCNO> FBIS3-12753 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes043_n_94001" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-043 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  4 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Islamic Battalions': U.S. Has 48 Hours To Leave </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0403113794 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 1122 GMT 4 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0403113794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Voice of Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A group calling itself the Islamic Battalions 
[al-kata'ib al-islamiyah] has threatened revenge for the martyrs 
of Palestine. The group said that hardline Islamists in Egypt 
will begin to attack the Americans and Israelis. 
  Carrying the report, REUTER said that the group made the 
threat in a statement seemingly faxed from Beirut. The 
statement gave the Americans in Egypt 48 hours to leave the 
country. The statement said: We warn every American in Egypt 
that he will be a target for the Islamist mujahidin in the 
country. 
  The group claimed responsibility for a device exploding in 
front of the Egyptian American Bank in Cairo last night. 
  The Islamic Group in Egypt earlier claimed responsibility 
for 
the same explosion as well as for recent attacks against banks 
and policemen in Egypt. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

