<H3> <TI>   Continued Commentaries, Reports on Church Bombing </TI></H3>
<H4>   Judge Appointed To Investigate </H4>
<F P=102> NC0403123194 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1130 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0403123194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Higher Judicial Council held a meeting under 
Judge Philip Khayrallah in al-Yarzah today [Defense Ministry's 
premises] to evaluate the findings of the security departments 
concerning the church massacre. Judge Nasri Lahhud, 
government-appointee to the military court; Judge Tarabay 
Rahmah, first attorney general for Mount Lebanon; and Riyad 
Tal'i, first military investigation judge; attended a part of 
the meeting. 
  After deliberations into the Sayyidat al-Najat Church 
massacre and reviewing new information, which the conferees 
unanimously decided to keep secret, the Higher Judicial Council 
approved a proposal by Justice Minister Bahij Tabbarah to 
appoint former Prosecutor General Judge Joseph Furayhah as 
investigating judge into the explosion. 

</TEXT>

