<H3> <TI>   AL-BA'TH Urges `Balanced' European Role in Peace Process </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2502135194 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 0545 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2502135194 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the press review] </F>
  [Text] In an editorial today, AL-BA'TH says: One can 
deduce from the Israeli conduct that there is a new attempt not 
only to circumvent the results of the Geneva summit, but also to 
circumvent the U.S. role and all the international efforts 
seeking to achieve the just and comprehensive peace in the 
region. 
  AL-BA'TH stresses the importance of having a balanced and 
effective European role in the peace process. However, the 
paper warns that the Israelis' emphasis on the Europeans, from 
the economic viewpoint, seeks to market the Oslo Agreement, in 
which some people found an opportunity to enter the region. The 
paper says: This view is based on a host of unfounded 
illusions, which will harm principally the peace process and the 
Europeans themselves, in view of their interests in the region 
and strong ties with the Arab states. The paper wonders: Will 
the European Community agree to serve as a bridge on which Rabin 
can cross to hamper the peace process? 
  AL-BA'TH concludes by saying: Israel has on more than one 
occasion tried to use the European role to its advantage. But 
that role remained balanced to some extent over the issue of the 
Arab-Israeli conflict. With Rabin's moves, which precede his 
visit to Washington, this role should not lose its balance 
because the wager on the Oslo Agreement will fail. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

