<H3> <TI>   Rabbani-Hekmatyar Clashes Continue in Kabul </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0303172094 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0303172094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Exchange of rocket and heavy weapons fire between 
the forces of Afghan President Borhanoddin Rabbani and Prime 
Minister Golboddin Hekmatyar shook Kabul once again today. 
  According to a report from Kabul, quoting Afghan Defense 
Ministry sources, the attacks took place in eastern areas of 
Kabul. In addition to inflicting heavy casualties and damage, 
the attacks caused some damage to the television station. The 
sources added: Hekmatyar forces were trying to seize the Pacha 
Bridge and eastern areas of Kabul, but government forces 
repelled them. 
  The attacks come at a time when various local commanders are 
trying to establish a cease-fire. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

