<H3> <TI>   Singh Discusses Pakistani Resolution With Western Envoys </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0303145594 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1430 
GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0303145594 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] India has sought closer cooperation of the European 
Union and the United States in dealing with Pakistan's 
resolution on Kashmir at the UN Human Rights Commission meeting 
in Geneva. The external affairs minister, Mr. Dinesh Singh, 
told the envoys of the European troika and the U.S. charge d' 
affaires in New Delhi today that neither the letter nor the 
spirit of the Pakistan resolution is acceptable to New Delhi. 
It will also not help in improving the situation in Jammu and 
Kashmir as it is the direct result of the Pakistan-sponsored 
terrorism. He asked them to convey India's position on the 
Pakistan resolution and hoped that the delegations of these 
countries will work closely with the Indian delegation in 
Geneva. The meeting was held at the request of the envoys. 

