<H4>   Foreign Ministers Meet </H4>
<F P=102> BK0303151194 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1430 
GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0303151194 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Poland today assured India that it will not support 
Pakistan's resolution on Kashmir at the UN Human Rights 
Commission meeting in Geneva. The visiting Polish foreign 
minister, Mr. (Andrzej Olechowski), gave this assurance in his 
talks with the external affairs minister, Mr. Dinesh Singh, in 
New Delhi. The Polish foreign minister said his country gives 
special emphasis to its relations with India and wants to 
strengthen the economic ties. 
  Mr. Dinesh Singh briefed him about Pakistan's attempt to 
internationalize the Kashmir issue under the guise of raising 
human rights issue. Pakistan's own record in this area is 
abysmal. Mr. Dinesh Singh said the political process in Jammu 
and Kashmir can easily begin if Pakistan stops aiding and 
abetting terrorism in the state. 
  Both also discussed the ongoing reforms in the UN system and 
called for making it more democratic. 

</TEXT>

