<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deputy Foreign Minister Receives Afghan Envoy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0203225194 Tehran IRNA in English 2152 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0203225194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, March, 2, IRNA -- Dr. Abdolrahman, personal 
envoy of the Afghan President Borhanoddin Rabbani, and Iran's 
Deputy Foreign Minister for Asia-Pacific Affairs 'Ala'eddin 
Borujerdi, here Wednesday discussed the recent developments in 
Afghanistan. 
  Abdolrahman praised Iran's humanitarian efforts to put an 
end 
to Afghan clashes and hoped for cessation of hostilities between 
the two sides. 
  Abdolrahman welcomed the assistance of the Iranian officials 
to Afghanistan in order to tackle its problems and said, "we 
trust in good intention of the Iranian officials". 
  Borujerdi referred to Iran's intense efforts to put an end 
to 
the Afghan clashes and reiterated that the Afghan war is in no 
one's benefit. 
  The Iranian official warned Afghan rival factions of the 
folly of destroying Afghan potentials and called on them not let 
the country to go on the brink of destruction. He also hoped 
for a speedy stop for Afghan war. 

</TEXT>

