<F P=100> Nepal </F>
<H3> <TI>   Koirala Regains Consciousness in Hospital </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0403113594 Hong Kong AFP in English 1100 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0403113594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] KATHMANDU, March 4 (AFP) -- Prime Minister Girija 
Prasad Koirala regained consciousness half an hour after being 
taken to hospital Friday [25 February] after he collapsed while 
delivering a speech in the house of representatives, a hospital 
source said. 
  "He is being thoroughly checked in order to determine his 
physical condition," the source said. 
  Earlier a medical source said Koirala had suffered a heart 
attack. 
  The prime minister was addressing parliament during a 
special 
session to debate a no-confidence motion introduced by the 
opposition. 
  A parliamnetary source said the special session had been 
postponed until March 7. 

</TEXT>

