<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Welcomes Bosnian-Croat Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0303151094 Islamabad PTV Television Network in English 
1400 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0303151094 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad PTV Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pakistan has welcomed the signing of agreements 
between Bosnia and Croatia for a bicommunal federation in Bosnia 
to be linked with Croatia in a confederation. A statement 
issued by the Foreign Office in Islamabad today said the 
government appreciates the role played by the United States in 
achieving this result and is confident that this accord, which 
follows closely the cease-fire concluded by the Bosnian 
Government and Croats last week, would bring about a lasting 
reconciliation between the two communities. The statement said 
the agreement reached in Washington between the Bosnian 
Government and the Croat community would mark a significant step 
toward a comprehensive peaceful settlement of the Bosnian 
conflict. Pakistan also welcomes the positive role played by 
the Russian Government in the reopening of the Tuzla airport, 
making possible humanitarian aid to the city. 

</TEXT>

