<F P=100> Sri Lanka </F>
<H3> <TI>   PRC's Qian Qichen Leaves Colombo for Maldives </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0203122194 Colombo Sri Lanka Broadcasting Corporation 
International Service in English 1045 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0203122194 </F>
<F P=104>  Colombo Sri Lanka Broadcasting Corporation 
International Service </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Chinese vice premier and foreign minister, Qian 
Qichen, concluding his three-day official visit to Sri Lanka 
left Colombo for the Maldives this morning. During his stay in 
the island, the Chinese leader held talks with President D.B. 
Wijetunga, Prime Minister Ranil Wickremasinghe, and Speaker M.H. 
Mohamed on ways and means of expanding economic cooperation 
between the two countries. He also held official talks with his 
Sri Lankan counterpart A.C. Shahul Hameed on bilateral relations 
and regional and international matters. The Chinese vice 
premier and his entourage were seen off at the Katunayaka 
International Airport by Foreign Minister Hameed and the Chinese 
ambassador in Sri Lanka, Zhang Chengli. Minister Hameed 
presented an album of photographs depicting the visitors, who 
were on the island, to the Chinese dignitary prior to his 
departure at the airport. 

</TEXT>

