Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  4 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Forms Committee To Probe Mosque Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0303140394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1235 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0303140394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, 3 Mar (MENA)--Palestinian President Yasir 
'Arafat has decided to set up an investigative committee made up 
of some prominent figures in the city of Hebron in the occupied 
West Bank to investigate the circumstances of the massacre that 
took place in al-Ibrahimi Mosque in Hebron last Friday. The 
Palestinian president's decision stipulates that this committee 
will cooperate with a committee of Arab lawyers in Jerusalem; 
the Research Center of the University Graduates' Association; 
Hebron University; and national, Arab, and international 
personalities, institutions, and associations. 
  The decision also stipulates that the committee begins work 
and submits its report to the PLO Executive Committee as soon as 
possible. 

</TEXT>

