Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] A well informed Palestinian source in Tunis last 
night confirmed that Yasir 'Abd-Rabbuh, the head of the PLO 
Information Department would arrive in Paris today to hold talks 
with French officials regarding the conditions of resuming 
Israeli-Palestinian economic talks, halted since the Hebron 
massacre. This is within the framework of what the PLO 
Executive Committee decided in its recent meetings regarding 
sending envoys to Western countries to explain its [PLO] 
conditions for resuming talks with Israel on the implementation 
of the agreement on Palestinian self-rule in Gaza and Jericho. 
  A French Foreign Ministry spokeswoman said yesterday that 
France, who is chairing the [UN] Security Council this month, 
was hoping for the Security Council's approval of a resolution 
very soon. The spokeswoman raised the [issue of the] need for 
the immediate implementation by the Israeli authorities of the 
measures taken against the settlers and those to the benefit of 
the Palestinians. [passage omitted] 

