<F P=102>  PM0303140194 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 3 Mar 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> PM0303140194 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "'Abd-al-Hamid al-Bakkush"] </F>
  [Text] London, AL-HAYAH -- Libyan opposition sources have 
said that they have lost contact with former Prime Minister 
'Abd-al-Hamid al-Bakkush for a week. 
  AL-HAYAH contacted al-Bakkush's family in Cairo. The family 
said that "he left the Egyptian capital a week ago for a 
destination which he did not reveal as usual." The family 
pointed out that "it is not worried about him at all, because he 
is used to traveling for long periods without revealing his 
destination." 

