<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Briefs U.S. Envoy on Latest Developments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0503232494 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 2200 GMT 5 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0503232494 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brother leader Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat] met U.S. 
Ambassador in Tunis John McCarthy yesterday evening. During the 
meeting, they reviewed the latest political developments and the 
dimensions and repercussions on the peace process and the 
current negotiations of the massacre at the holy Ibrahimi mosque 
perpetrated by Zionist settlers. 
  They also reviewed the deliberations of the UN Security 
Council regarding a resolution on the massacre perpetrated by 
the settlers, the need to guarantee international protection for 
our Palestinian people, and the disarming of the Zionist 
settlers so that such a massacre would not be repeated. 
  They also reviewed the Palestinian-U.S. meeting chaired by 
Dr. Nabil Sha'th [as heard], which is currently being held with 
U.S. officials in Washington so that the Security Council can 
come up with an effective resolution. 
  The meeting was attended on the Palestinian side by brother 
Abu-Lutf [Faruq Qaddumi], the head of the PLO Political 
Department, Brother Hayil al-Fahum, the head of the European 
section in the political department, and Dr. Sami Musallam, head 
of the president's office. 

</TEXT>

