<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Contacts Said Under Way for 'Arafat-Peres Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0603204594 Sanaa Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1800 GMT 6 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0603204594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Voice of Palestine </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to Israeli radio, the PLO and the Israeli 
Government are holding contacts about a possible meeting today 
or tomorrow between brother Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat] and 
Shim'on Peres, who will try to talk him into resuming the 
negotiations. Peres sent a message to brother Abu-'Ammar 
regarding expediting the withdrawal from the Gaza Strip and the 
Jericho area, boosting the size of the Palestinian police force, 
taking over immediate [as heard] responsibility for the Strip 
and Jericho, and the deployment of international observers in 
the projected Palestinian self-rule area. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-12812 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes044dd_94004" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-044 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  7 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

