<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Negotiators Reject Israeli Demand on Collaborators </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0203153094 Jerusalem AL-QUDS in Arabic 2 Mar 94 pp 1, 18 </F>
<F P=103> TA0203153094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem AL-QUDS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Sa'idah Hamad] </F>
  [Excerpt] Ramallah, QUDS PRESS -- Professor Bassam Jarrar 
and Dr. Mahmud al-Zahhar, Palestinian negotiators in the talks 
for implementing the self-rule accord, have warned against 
"capitulating" to Israeli demands regarding the release of 
prisoners in return for providing protection to collaborators 
with the Israeli forces. 
  Bassam Jarrar, a leading Ramallah dignitary, has said that 
"Israel is interested in providing protection for its agents." 
He pointed out that giving guarantees that no harm will befall 
collaborators with the occupation in exchange for the release of 
detainees held by the authorities aims at "encouraging those 
individuals and others to collaborate with Israel." He added: 
This will set a dangerous precedent that will help Israel to 
continue recruiting collaborators even after the self-rule 
accord is implemented. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

