<H3> <TI>   Hamas Denies Report on Halt to Retaliation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0603210494 Amman AKHIR KHABAR in Arabic 6-7 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN0603210494 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AKHIR KHABAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Letter to AKHIR KHABAR from "the Hamas Movement;" place </F>
and date not given] 
  [Text] Editor-in-chief of AKHIR KHABAR: 
  Peace be upon you. Your newspaper published a front-page 
report on 5 March headlined "Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat] Orders 
Not To Retaliate" which says that sources close to the Hamas 
Movement told you that the Palestinian leadership hopes Hamas 
will not carry out any military operations at present, and that 
Hamas has halfheartedly responded to this request. 
  We emphasize that this report is baseless and that all 
information contained in this report is a total fabrication. 
  No contacts have taken place between our movement and the 
Palestinian leadership on retaliation for the Hebron massacre. 
Our movement's policy is clear and open. It calls for strong 
and decisive retaliation against the holy Ibrahimi Mosque 
massacre and revenge for the martyrs' blood. 
  Our position has always rejected the Oslo and Cairo 
agreements, and this fully conflicts with the published report. 
  While we wish that you would check such information through 
contacting the known Hamas representatives in the future, we 
hope that you will publish this clarification in the same place 
in which that report was published. [no signature as published] 

</TEXT>

