<F P=101> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   MENA Previews Upcoming Mubarak, Arafat Talks </TI></H3>
<H4>   'Arafat Meets French President's Envoy </H4>
<F P=102> NC0703123394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1105 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0703123394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 7 Mar (MENA)--Palestinian President Yasir 
'Arafat has received French President Francois Mitterrand's 
adviser, Bruno Dulain [name and title as received], at his 
residence in Cairo. 
  Palestinian sources in Cairo told MENA that during the 
meeting they discussed the obstacles hindering the 
Palestinian-Israeli peace talks in light of the massacre the 
Israeli settlers committed against the Palestinian worshipers in 
the al-Ibrahimi Mosque and the world reaction to it. 
  Palestinian Ambassador Sa'id Kamal attended the meeting, 
which was held yesterday evening. 

</TEXT>

