<H3> <TI>   Mubarak, Saudi King Discuss Rights of Palestinians </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0503210394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2045 GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0503210394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 5 Mar (MENA)--President Husni Mubarak 
received a telephone call this evening from King Fahd 
Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz, custodian of the two holy mosques. They 
exchanged views on a number of issues of interest to the two 
countries, chief among them reaction to the incident at the 
al-Ibrahimi Mosque. They also discussed coordinating the two 
countries' positions and the measures that need to be taken to 
preserve the rights of Palestinians residing in the occupied 
territories and ensure their protection and security against 
future criminal incidents. 

</TEXT>

