<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Palestinian Envoy: Settlements To Top Agenda </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0503214294 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 2100 GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0503214294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Dr. Sa'ib 'Urayqat, head of the Palestinian 
delegation to the peace talks, has stressed the need for the 
issue of settlements to top the agenda of any 
Palestinian-Israeli talks in the future. In a statement to our 
radio, he pointed out that failing to include the question of 
settlements in the Palestinian-Israeli peace talks will make 
these talks pointless. He noted that the Palestinian side had 
called for the need to discuss the question of settlements 
before the Oslo agreement was signed to ensure protection for 
the Palestinians. 
  Dr. 'Urayqat added that the Palestinian people want peace 
more than any other party. He expressed fears for the possible 
recurrence of the Israeli massacres against citizens in the 
occupied Arab territories. He emphasized the need for 
international protection to ensure that such incidents may not 
recur in the future. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

