<F P=101> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Resolution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0503160494 Paris AFP in English 1516 GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0503160494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, March 5 (AFP)--The Iranian parliament on 
Saturday [5 March] called for a Palestinian armed struggle 
against Israel until the Jewish state disappeared from the face 
of the earth. 
  "We declare that the problem of Zionism will only be solved 
through armed struggle against Israel until the cancerous tumor 
disappears from the map of the world," said a statement from 
deputies, read out in parliament. 
  The deputies condemned the February 25 massacre of Moslem 
worshipers by a Jewish settler in the West Bank town of Hebron, 
and warned against using the "painful tragedy" as a catalyst for 
progress in the Arab-Israeli peace talks. 
  They also slammed the international community's "treacherous 
silence" over the "shocking crime." 
  Palestinian doctors say 52 Arabs were killed in the 
shooting, 
while the Israeli army has put the toll at 30. 
  On Friday Iranian spiritual guide Ayatollah 'Ali Khamene'i 
called for a massive uprising against Israel, with the backing 
of the Islamic world. 
  Fathi al-Shiqaqi, head of the fundamentalist Islamic Jihad 
in 
Palestine group, vowed here Saturday that Palestinian militants 
would soon launch revenge attacks against Israel in retaliation 
for the Hebron massacre. 

</TEXT>

