<H3> <TI>   Officials Discuss Developments in Church Bombing </TI></H3>
<H4>   Muslim Figure Accuses Israel </H4>
<F P=102> NC0503072094 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 0530 GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0503072094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shaykh Muhammad Mahdi Shams-al-Din, deputy chairman 
of the Higher Islamic Shiite Council, has renewed his accusation 
that Israel engineered the massacre at Sayyidat al-Najat Church. 
He stressed that this is a type of crime that only Israel 
commits. He did not rule out the possibility that the 
perpetrators may be Lebanese Christians, Maronites, or Muslims, 
adding: We exonerate no one; the crime happened and its 
perpetrators are at large in our society. And Israel has tools 
and agents in Lebanon. He went on to call on the government to 
uncover the criminals because we want to learn the identity of 
these tools of Israel. 
  Grand Ja'farite Mufti Shaykh 'Abd-al-Amir Qabalan has said 
that the total condemnation of the Sayyidat al-Najah Church 
crime has fortified Lebanon anew, enhanced the Lebanese people's 
vigilance and cohesion, and consolidated their national unity. 

</TEXT>

