<H3> <TI>   Rabin Says Implementation Possible in 6 Weeks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0403141994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1300 GMT 4 Feb 
93 </F>

<F P=103> TA0403141994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin said that the 
Gaza-Jericho agreement can be implemented within six weeks. Our 
political correspondent Shlomo Raz reports that Mr. Rabin made 
the remarks to an EC delegation led by the Greek foreign 
minister. The prime minister also said in the meeting that he 
would be ready to accept an international presence only in Gaza 
and Jericho after the Palestinians take over those areas. He 
also told the guests that Israel is interested in the resumption 
of the negotiations with the PLO as soon as possible, but he 
would not be prepared to reopen agreed upon accords. 

