<H3> <TI>   Al-Bid Announces Halt to Media Campaign </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0703112294 Amman SAWT AL-SHA'B in Arabic 7 Mar 94 p 24 </F>
<F P=103> JN0703112294 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman SAWT AL-SHA'B </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Aden, QNA [Qatari News Agency]--'Ali Salim al-Bid, 
Yemeni vice president and leader of the Yemeni Socialist Party 
[YSP], has announced a unilateral halt to what he termed 
vituperations and media campaigns, as of yesterday. 
  In a message to the Yemeni people, broadcast over Aden Radio 
last night, al-Bid said the decision was made by the YSP 
Political Bureau in observance of the citizens' sorrow over the 
death of former Yemeni President 'Abdallah al-Sallal and out of 
respect for the last holy days of Ramadan. 
  The vice president said in this regard: The decision, made 
under serious circumstances, reflected great sorrow over the 
death of Field Marshal 'Abdallah al-Sallal and our feelings 
about this mournful event. 

