<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   MENA Previews Upcoming Mubarak, Arafat Talks </TI></H3>
<H4>   Official Comments </H4>
<F P=102> NC0403155194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1358 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0403155194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 4 Mar (MENA)--Palestinian President Yasir 
'Arafat will arrive in Cairo within the next 48 hours for a 
visit to Egypt during the visit, he will hold urgent 
consultations with President Husni Mubarak on the latest 
developments after the al-Ibrahimi Mosque massacre in Hebron. 
  'Arafat will meet with Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa and Dr. 
Usamah al-Baz, director of President Mubarak's Office for 
Political Affairs. He and the Egyptian officials will discuss 
ways to achieve the Palestinian demands that the PLO has set as 
conditions for the resumption of peace talks with Israel. The 
PLO suspended its participation in these talks because of the 
al-Ibrahimi Mosque massacre. 
  Palestinian Ambassador in Cairo Sa'id Kamal said 
Egypt--President Mubarak, the government, and the great 
people--has been and will remain the main supporter of the Arab 
and Palestinian people. 
  In a statement to MENA, he added that the growing support of 
the Egyptian and Arab nations for the condition of the 
Palestinian people in the occupied territories following the 
al-Ibrahimi Mosque massacre confirms Egypt's continuing, 
pioneering role in maintaining pan-Arab security. 

</TEXT>

