<H4>   'Arafat, Mubarak Talks Begin </H4>
<F P=102> NC0603181794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1755 GMT 6 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0603181794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 6 Mar (MENA)--Talks between President Husni 
Mubarak and Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat began at the 
presidential office this evening. Members of the Egyptian and 
Palestinian sides attended. 
  The two sides reviewed the latest developments in the 
Palestinian problem in light of recent events in the area, 
particularly the massacre in the Ibrahimi Mosque in Hebron. 
  The Egyptian side to the talks consists of Foreign Minister 
'Amr Musa and Dr. Usamah al-Baz, first Foreign Ministry under 
secretary and director of the president's Office for Political 
Affairs. The Palestinian side includes PLO Executive Committee 
member Jamal Surani, Palestine Ambassador in Cairo Sa'id Kamal, 
and Fatah representative in Cairo Zuhdi al-Qidrah. 

