<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deputies' Resolution Offers Solution to Zionism `Problem' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0503172094 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0503172094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to a report by our correspondent, a 
resolution signed by more than 140 deputies was read during the 
Majles open session this afternoon condemning the horrific 
crimes of the Zionists in Hebron and the mysterious and 
treacherous silence of international forums and false supporters 
of human rights. 
  The resolution--expressing support for His Eminence Imam 
Khomeyni's justified stand on the need for the elimination of 
the Zionist regime from the world map and following the esteemed 
leader's stand--has emphasized: The solution to the problem of 
Zionism and uprooting of this cancerous tumor will not be 
possible except through continuation of the armed conflict. 
  The resolution, in part, says: What is tragic in the wake of 
this painful development is the fact that global arrogance--led 
by America and criminal Zionism--has declared the occurrence of 
this tragedy as solid preparation for continuation of the 
compromising talks and has expressed the need for speeding up 
the sell-out plan. 
  In the conclusion of the resolution, the deputies of the 
Islamic Majles have called upon our country's noble and 
revolutionary people and all freedom loving people and Muslims 
of the world to pour out the fire of their revolutionary wrath 
and anger against the usurping Zionism, through enthusiastic 
participation in rallies of the international Jerusalem Day, and 
to repay their debt to the unjustly shed blood of the innocent 
Palestinians by chanting slogans of death to Israel and death to 
America. 

</TEXT>

