<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat's Talk With Rabin's Aide Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0703190294 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1830 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0703190294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The radio's central news unit correspondent has 
learned that Jacques Neriya, Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq 
Rabin's political adviser, met with Palestinian President Yasir 
'Arafat in Cairo today. The Israeli envoy presented the 
Palestinian president specific Israeli ideas on overcoming the 
crisis resulting from the attack on worshipers in the 
al-Ibrahimi Mosque and on creating a general climate that will 
allow the PLO to resume the negotiations. 
  President 'Arafat discussed with the Israeli prime 
minister's 
adviser the measures that have to be taken to protect the 
Palestinians in the Arab territories. These measures include 
the protection of the Palestinians, provision of security for 
them, and a nonrepetition of the Hebron incident. 
  The radio correspondent also learned that the Palestinian 
side stressed the importance of disarming the settlers, 
restricting or dissolving the extremist organizations, removing 
the settlers from Hebron and densely populated Palestinian 
areas, and providing the necessary protection for the 
Palestinians. 
  President 'Arafat met with Neriya before the former's 
departure from Cairo this afternoon. 

</TEXT>

