<H3> <TI>   League Sends Messages to Security Council Members </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0703122794 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1000 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0703122794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Arab League Secretary General Dr. 'Ismat 
'Abd-al-Majid today sent urgent messages to the five permanent 
members of the UN Security Council prior to the council's 
meeting later today to adopt a resolution on the Israeli 
massacre of Palestinians in the al-Ibrahimi Mosque in Hebron. 
  In the messages, 'Abd-al-Majid voiced all Arab states' 
concern at the council's delay in adopting a resolution 
condemning the massacre 10 days after it was committed. 

</TEXT>

