<H3> <TI>   Cordon States To Meet on Suspension of Negotiations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0703124094 Amman AL-RA'Y in Arabic 7 Mar 94 p 29 </F>
<F P=103> JN0703124094 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-RA'Y </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Sa'd al-Silawi] </F>
  [Excerpt] Informed Palestinian sources have mentioned that 
intensive contacts are under way to convene a meeting of the 
cordon states in Cairo. 
  The sources did not specify the proposed date for this 
meeting. However, they emphasized that all parties have agreed 
to hold such a meeting in which the foreign ministers of Jordan, 
Syria, Lebanon, Egypt, and the PLO will take part. 
  The sources said that the meeting's agenda will cover the 
suspension of negotiations with Israel in light of the 25 
February Hebron massacre. [passage omitted] 

