<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Abd-al-Shafi Urges PLO To Suspend Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0303194194 Jerusalem AL-QUDS in Arabic 3 Mar 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> TA0303194194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem AL-QUDS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Nicosia -- In his first reaction to the Ibrahimi 
Mosque massacre, Dr. Haydar 'Abd-al-Shafi, former head of the 
Palestinian negotiating delegation, has said that this ugly and 
criminal act reminds one of previous and repeated massacres to 
which the Palestinian people have been subjected in Dayr Yasin, 
Kafr Qasim, the al-Aqsa Mosque, Qibya, and Nahalin. 
  'Abd-al-Shafi was speaking by phone with AL-QUDS from 
Nicosia, where he is visiting at present in response to an 
invitation to attend an international conference of churches 
after paying a visit to South Africa. 
  Dr. 'Abd-al-Shafi added that a good solution cannot be 
reached except with the removal of Israeli settlements from the 
heart of the West Bank and Gaza Strip. Settlements are the main 
obstacle to the achievement of a lasting peace in the region on 
the basis of UN resolutions. 
  'Abd-al-Shafi called on the Palestinian leadership to 
suspend 
the talks and reassess the current Palestinian situation 
entirely on a democratic basis. This would ensure the unity of 
the Palestinian position inside and outside by mobilizing all 
Palestinian potentials and defining the effective options 
available to the Palestinian people. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

