<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Statement Issued on Ivanov-'Arafat Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0203231694 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 2200 GMT 2 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0203231694 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Press statement issued by the Russian press office in Tunis </F>
on 1 March] 
  [Text] Russian President Boris Yeltsin decided to send his 
personal envoy to carry out consultations with the leadership of 
the PLO within the existing framework of Russian-Palestinian 
cooperation to resolve issues involving a Middle East settlement. 
  President Yasir 'Arafat received a personal letter from 
President Boris Yeltsin in which he expressed Russia's strong 
intentions to help on all fronts to reach comprehensive peace 
and security in the Middle East. 
  Yasir 'Arafat expressed deep appreciation for the support 
that the Russian president was giving Palestinian people during 
these difficult times. He pointed out Russia's important role 
in the Middle East. 
  The meeting with the Palestinian leader focused on steps 
aimed at preserving the peace process in the light of the 
current tension in the occupied territories after the Hebron 
tragedy. 
  The Russian side expressed support for the Palestinian 
position on the necessity of securing an international presence 
in the occupied territories that would become an additional 
guarantee against the possible recurrence of such provocative 
acts. 
  President 'Arafat received with appreciation the Russian 
decision to provide practical aid to establish Palestinian 
self-rule. With the importance of Russian-Palestinian 
cooperation in the peace process in mind, an agreement was 
reached to continue close contacts. 

</TEXT>

