<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Security Termed Essential for Peace </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0703094094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0726 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0703094094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 7 Mar (MENA)--AL-JUMHURIYAH demands that 
security be provided for the Palestinian people as a first step 
toward ending the occupation because this is the only way to 
bring about a just, lasting, and comprehensive peace. 
  In an editorial today, the paper says that the al-Ibrahimi 
Mosque massacre revealed the serious dimensions of the Middle 
East conflict and proved that working for a just and 
comprehensive peace involving all parties concerned means 
providing security for all parties. It does not mean securing 
the existence of one party at the expense of the other. 
  AL-JUMHURIYAH emphasizes that real peace requires ending all 
racist trends and discrediting all claims about the right to use 
force to expand into other people's lands and that peace means 
coexistence and cooperation without discrimination. Since the 
Palestinian people are disarmed under the occupation, the 
settlers living on lands they will never be entitled to under 
any circumstances must be disarmed, the paper stresses. 
  AL-JUMHURIYAH affirms that Egypt will continue to back the 
Palestinian people with its firm, solid, and effective stances 
because this is the destiny it accepts willingly. 

</TEXT>

