<H3> <TI>   Students Plan March to Israel Embassy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0703194394 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0703194394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] University students in Egypt have issued a statement 
calling for Egyptian volunteers to be sent to occupied Palestine 
to engage in jihad against the Zionists. 
  Dr. Badr-al-Din Ghazi, head of the Cairo University Teachers 
Association, announced the formation of an university committee 
for the boycott of the Zionist entity. The committee will press 
for the severing of ties between Egypt and the Zionist entity 
and the expulsion of the Zionist ambassador in Cairo. 
  Islamic student societies and the Cairo University Teachers 
Association have announced plans to stage a massive march 
tomorrow [8 March] following a prayer service for the souls of 
the victims of the al-Ibrahimi Mosque massacre. The march will 
proceed to the Zionist embassy in Cairo to express outrage at 
the Hebron massacre. 

</TEXT>

