<H3> <TI>   Editorial Criticizes Security Council's `Slackness' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0703095594 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0730 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0703095594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 7 Mar (MENA)--AL-AKHBAR criticizes the UN 
Security Council, which still refuses to issue a clear, 
forthright resolution condemning the Israeli Government for the 
al-Ibrahimi Mosque massacre in which hundreds were killed and 
wounded by an armed Jewish extremist. Later, more were killed 
and wounded by the Israeli Army during demonstrations to protest 
the massacre. 
  In an editorial today, the newspaper says that if some 
states 
defend the UN Security Council's slackness regarding 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and the al-Ibrahimi Mosque massacre using the 
excuse that certain powers obstruct any decisive resolution, the 
world cannot stand by when it sees this important authority 
become too weak to play the role entrusted to it by the UN 
Charter. 
  AL-AKHBAR calls for referring the matter to the UN General 
Assembly to take the necessary measures to restore the UN 
Security Council's esteem. 

</TEXT>

