<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Envoy to Israel Comments on Syrian Role in Peace Process </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0803074994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2215 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0803074994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Damascus, 7 Mar (MENA)--Muhammad Basyuni, Egypt's 
ambassador to Israel, has affirmed that Syria is the key to 
comprehensive peace, without it, there can be no comprehensive 
peace in the region. 
  This came in an interview with the Egyptian ambassador 
published in one of the Israeli Arab newspapers of which some 
issues were distributed in Damascus by the Arab Israeli 
delegation currently visiting Damascus. 
  Ambassador Basyuni clarified that despite the difficulty in 
the Syrian-Israeli peace track, it has clear characteristics. 
He noted that a comprehensive peace between Israel and Syria 
cannot be reached without full Israeli withdrawal from the Golan 
Heights. 
  He affirmed that Syria cannot accept anything less than full 
withdrawal in return for comprehensive peace. 
  He pointed out that peace is the essential demand of all 
people in the region without exception. He expects that 1994 
will be the year of peace in which agreements on the Declaration 
of Principles will be signed on all peace tracks. 
  As regards reports on terrorism in Egypt, the Egyptian 
ambassador affirmed in his interview that what is being reported 
about this topic is exaggerated. Violence and terrorism are an 
international phenomenon from which many progressive and 
developed countries are suffering. It is not restricted to 
Egypt alone. 

</TEXT>

