<H3> <TI>   European Union Delegation in Damascus for Talks </TI></H3>
<H4>   Meets With al-Shar' </H4>
<F P=102> JN0503215694 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 2115 GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0503215694 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] An official round of talks was held this evening 
at the Foreign Ministry between Syria and the European Union 
[EU]. Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar' led the Syrian team and 
Mr. Karolos Papoulias, the Greek foreign minister, whose country 
holds the current presidency of the EU, led the European side. 
The talks were also joined by EU Commissioner General Hans Van 
den Broek; Yusuf Shakkur, Syria's assistant foreign minister; 
and the directors of the Economic Department, Western Europe 
Department, and the Information Department. For the EU side, 
the meeting was also attended by Mr. (Khristos Zakharakis), 
director general of the Greek Foreign Ministry; the director 
general of bilateral relations at the ministry; and Mr. (Sham 
Kunwa), an ambassador at the EU; and Mr. Yeorios Yennimatas, the 
Greek ambassador in Damascus. 
  Discussions reviewed Middle East developments in light of 
the 
Ibrahimi Mosque massacre and its serious implications for the 
situation in the occupied Arab territories, the region, and the 
peace process. 
  Mr. al-Shar' pointed to the unending obstacles Israel places 
in the path of peace, and its lack of seriousness in the search 
for a fair and comprehensive peace in the region. Europe's 
potential role in the peace process and Syrian-EU cooperation 
was also discussed. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

