<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   European Union Delegation in Damascus for Talks </TI></H3>
<H4>   Received by al-Asad </H4>
<F P=102> JN0603174694 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1615 GMT 6 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0603174694 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At 1230 today, His Excellency President Hafiz 
al-Asad received Greek Foreign Minister Karolos Papoulias, 
current chairman of the European Union [EU], and the delegation 
accompanying him. Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar' and the Greek 
ambassador attended. 
  Papoulias handed a letter to the president from Greek Prime 
Minister Andreas Papandreou dealing with the peace process and 
bilateral relations. Papoulias expressed the condolences of the 
EU Council of Ministers on the death of Staff Major Basil 
al-Asad. Talks then centered on the peace process in the region, 
as well as the EU delegation's mission on its current tour. 
  President al-Asad stressed Syria's support for the peace 
process despite Israel's unserious stand on the peace process 
and despite doubts about Israel's seriousness. The president 
also recalled that Syria has repeatedly called for an active 
European role to help the peace process achieve progress. 
  The EU delegation, which was headed by Greek Foreign 
Minister 
Karolos Papoulias, current chairman of the EU, and which 
included EU Commissioner General Hans Van den Broek, left 
Damascus this afternoon after a two-day visit to Syria. They 
was seen off at Damascus International Airport by Foreign 
Minister Faruq al-Shar', Assistant Foreign Minister Yusuf 
Shakkur, several senior Foreign Ministry officials, and the 
Greek ambassador in Damascus and the embassy staff. 
  In a statement to SANA correspondent, Papoulias said: My 
visit to Syria was very constructive and positive. I met with 
President Hafiz al-Asad in my capacity as chairman of the EU 
Council of Ministers. I also met with Vice President 
'Abd-al-Halim Khaddam and Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar'. A 
cordial and warm atmosphere prevailed in all these meetings. He 
added: At these meetings we discussed a series of issues, 
foremost of which is the situation in the region, the 
possibility of promoting the peace process, and EU- Syrian 
relations. Papoulias also said: In my capacity as Greece's 
foreign minister, we discussed bilateral relations. The results 
of these talks were very good, and I will convey the concepts 
and views of the Syrian leaders to my colleagues, the foreign 
ministers of the EU member states. All these views are very 
important and will help us make decisions at the EU regarding 
future steps we will take. 

</TEXT>

