<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Khaddam Receives Lebanese Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0603073894 (Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon in Arabic 0545 
GMT 6 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0603073894 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Lebanese question moved to Syria yesterday, 
where Prime Minister Rafiq al-Hariri met with Syrian Vice 
President 'Abd-al-Halim Khaddam over an Iftar banquet held in 
al-Hariri's honor. According to unconfirmed reports from 
Damascus, the prime minister, who stayed the night in Syria, may 
meet with President Hafiz al-Asad before returning to Beirut 
today. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

