<H3> <TI>   Citizens Can Buy, Sell Foreign Currency in Banks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0703161394 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1520 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0703161394 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 7 Mar (INA)--A responsible source at the 
Iraqi Central Bank has confirmed that foreign currency can be 
bought and sold through the branches of the licensed commercial 
banks in Baghdad and the governorates and through the companies 
licensed to buy and sell foreign currencies. 
  In a statement to INA, the source said that these branches 
and companies have the financial and technical resources to help 
citizens buy and sell foreign currencies easily and in a 
legitimate way. Such dealings, the source added, will also 
ensure a safe dealing in national and foreign currencies. 

</TEXT>

