<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Reportedly Cancels Jordanian Transport Contracts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0803090094 Amman AKHIR KHABAR in Arabic 7-8 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN0803090094 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AKHIR KHABAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Jumanah Halasah] </F>
  [Text] The Iraqi Ministry of Transport has canceled all 
contracts with Jordanian transportation firms. Observers say 
this measure will paralyze a large sector of the Jordanian 
economy. 
  AKHIR KHABAR has learned that Iraq will confine 
transportation to the Iraqi-Jordanian Land Transport Company. 
Iraq did not explain this measure or announce it; it 
implemented it on the ground. Sources told us that Jordanian 
transportation firms are trying to take a unified stand and 
address the Jordanian and Iraqi Governments in order to explain 
the extent of damage they will sustain. 
  It is noteworthy that approximately 80 percent of these 
firms' work is devoted to Iraq. This shows the size of this 
problem. Truck drivers are living in extremely difficult 
conditions at the Iraqi-Jordanian border area of al-Ruwayshid. 
AKHIR KHABAR has learned that world television networks will 
today begin to raise this problem as a political issue, taking 
pictures of the al- Ruwayshid area. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

