<H3> <TI>   Dialogue Committee Views Implementation of Accord </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0803074794 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
2000 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0803074794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Within the framework of the political forces' 
efforts to practically implement the document of pledge and 
accord signed in Amman on 10 Ramadan [20 February], the 
Political Forces' Dialogue Committee met at the Prime Ministry 
at noon today under the chairmanship of brother 'Abd-al-'Aziz 
'Abd-al-Ghani, member of the Presidential Council. 
  The meeting was devoted to discussing the role of the 
Political Forces' Dialogue Committee in following and 
supervising the implementation of all aspects of the document in 
the light of the topics listed on the Committee's agenda. 
Following deliberations, the Dialogue Committee (?asked) the 
committees it formed to expedite the drafting of the required 
concepts in implementation of the relevant decisions. These 
committees are: The Security Committee, the Political and 
Military Committee, the Information Committee, and the committee 
in charge of drawing up a working program to follow up and 
supervise the implementation of the accord. These committees 
will present their plans to the Political Forces' Dialogue 
Committee meeting, which will be held the day after tomorrow, 
Wednesday. 

