<H3> <TI>   Salih Orders Ramadan Release of 1,400 Prisoners </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0803075494 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
2000 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0803075494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A responsible source at the public prosecution has 
told the Yemeni News Agency, SABA', that brother Lieutenant 
General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, chairman of the Presidential 
Council, has ordered the release of 1,400 male and female 
prisoners in the capital and the governorates of Aden, Ta'izz, 
Hadramaut, al-Hudaydah, Ibb, Dhamar, Hajjah, al-Mahwit, and 
al-Bayda', who have served more than half of their prison terms 
for crimes they committed and whose good conduct has been 
confirmed. This step is taken on the occasion of the blessed 
month of Ramadan. 
  The brother chairman of the Presidential Council, chairman 
of 
the higher judiciary council, has also instructed the competent 
quarters to pay those who could not pay the blood money or fines 
decided by court against them and to overlook the terms to which 
they were sentenced in administrative and other lawsuits. 

